name: ethanol production from sugar beet | ethanol, without water, in 95% solution state, from fermentation | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/7570/documentation

The multioutput-process "sugar beets, to fermentation" delivers the co-products Ethanol, 95% in H20, from sugar beets",  "beets chips", and vinasse. The allocation is based on  economic criteria. World production of ethanol from sugar beets is around 10 Mio hl per year.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Fermentation of sugar beets including materials, energy uses, infrastructure, and emissions.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The inventory is modelled with data from a plant in Finland.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Production of ethanol from sugar beets with extraction, fermentation, and distillation of ethanol.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Some data are derived from other or unknown plants or have been estimated. This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
